\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Title: Dunning emails: best practices with 8 examples\
slug: dunning-emails\
Meta des: Learn how to write a dunning email that recovers failed payments, reduces churn, and keeps your customer relationships intact with these tips and examples.\
Let\'92s be honest\'97no one gets excited about failed payments.\
But here\'92s the good news: most of them are fixable.\
In fact, research from Recurly shows that nearly three out of four payment failures can be recovered with the right approach. That\'92s a 
\f1\i lot
\f0\i0  of revenue just waiting to be rescued.\
Whether you\'92re brand new to dunning or just looking to tighten up your strategy, I\'92ve got you covered.\
From real-world examples (yep, straight from my inbox) to practical tips and copy tweaks, this guide is your go-to for turning awkward billing moments into smooth saves.\
Ready? Let\'92s dive in.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs36 \cf0 What is a dunning email (and why it\'92s your subscription safety net)?\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 A dunning email is a payment reminder sent to customers when a recent payment fails\'97usually due to issues like expired credit cards, insufficient funds, or declined payments. While it might sound formal (or even a little medieval), it\'92s actually a friendly, modern tool used by subscription businesses to recover payments and avoid service interruption.\
The goal? Keep the customer relationship intact while gently guiding them back to an active account. A successful dunning email includes clear payment information, a prominent call to action, and a tone that encourages prompt attention without sounding pushy.\
Whether you're notifying customers of an overdue payment or a final notice before account suspension, dunning messages can help subscription companies reduce involuntary churn and keep cash flow steady. When written well, they're more than reminders\'97they're customer communication lifelines that {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.digistorms.com/blog/user-engagement-strategy"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 \ul \ulc3 \strokec3 support both revenue and retention}}.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs28 \cf0 Why failed payments happen more often than you think\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 Failed payments are surprisingly common\'97even when a customer wants to stay subscribed. Most payment issues stem from everyday problems like expired credit cards, insufficient funds, or billing errors during the payment process. For SaaS and subscription companies, these hiccups can quickly snowball into missed payments and, eventually, involuntary churn.\
Sometimes, it\'92s a simple case of outdated billing information or a temporary hold on the customer\'92s payment method. Other times, it\'92s a declined payment due to fraud flags or credit limits. Regardless of the reason, these payment and billing issues affect your cash flow and customer accounts.\
The good news? With the right dunning strategy in place, you can recover payments quickly and painlessly\'97often before the customer even notices there's a problem.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs28 \cf0 The dunning process: how payment recovery actually works\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 The dunning process is a structured, multi-step approach to resolving failed payments and collecting overdue payments before they lead to service suspension. It typically starts with a pre dunning email\'97sent before the due date\'97to remind customers of an upcoming charge and prompt them to check their payment details.\
If the payment fails, automated dunning emails kick in. These messages notify the customer of the outstanding balance, provide a clear payment page link, and include a personalized message or subject line designed to encourage action.\
The process may include multiple payment reminders spaced out over time, increasing in urgency with each attempt. A final notice is usually sent before account suspension, giving customers a last chance to update their payment information.\
When done right, the dunning process reduces non payment, improves billing system efficiency, and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.digistorms.com/blog/net-revenue-retention"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 \ul \ulc3 \strokec3 helps subscription businesses recover revenue}} without damaging the customer relationship.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

