\f2\b\fs28 \cf0 Loom\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 Loom started with a standard Stripe-powered dunning message\'97clean, branded, but pretty generic. Then, just one minute later, they followed up with their own email, and that\'92s where it got better.\
The tone was friendly, the call to action was clear (\'93Pay now\'94), and they even personalized it with my company name. I appreciated that they reminded me of what I\'92d lose by not paying\'97features like unlimited videos and engagement insights.\
A week later, they sent the exact same email again. Consistent follow-up, human tone, and a benefits-focused reminder? That\'92s a solid dunning strategy in my book.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
