\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 Freepik\'92s dunning emails were consistent, structured, and rich in payment details. I received the first one after a failed payment, followed by two reminders over the next few days.\
Each message included the amount due, the last four digits of my card, exact timestamps, and even the reason for the failure (\'93Fund / Limit Issue\'94). That level of transparency builds trust and reduces confusion. The call to action\'97\'93Reactivate my subscription\'94\'97was easy to spot and well-placed.\
While the emails weren\'92t particularly warm or branded, they nailed the basics of dunning management with clarity, timing, and helpful payment information.\
