\cf0 Google Workspace\'92s dunning email is everything you\'92d expect from a big-name SaaS: professional, clear, and focused on process.\
It outlines exactly what happened (a failed payment), what to do next, and what the consequences are\'97
\f1\i service suspension for all users
\f0\i0  if not resolved by a specific date. The message includes helpful links for fixing billing issues and contacting the support team.\
While it\'92s not warm or particularly human, it nails the essentials of dunning management: clear payment instructions, a due date, and step-by-step guidance. It\'92s more transactional than personal\'97but it gets the job done with minimal friction.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs28 \cf0 Canva\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 Canva\'92s dunning email strikes a great balance between clarity and friendliness. It explains the payment failure in plain language and offers multiple suggestions\'97like checking if the saved payment method is still valid or trying a different card.\
There\'92s a specific payment deadline, a visible CTA button, and a gentle reminder about what features I\'92d lose if the issue isn\'92t resolved. It\'92s practical without being alarmist. Plus, the footer reinforces that this is a necessary account email, not marketing fluff.\
All in all, Canva\'92s approach feels thoughtful, supportive, and well-aligned with their user-first brand.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
