\f2\b\fs36 \cf0 Dunning messages across channels\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 Email is great\'97but it\'92s not your only tool for recovering failed payments. By expanding your dunning strategy across channels, you\'92ll reach customers faster and more effectively, wherever they are.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs28 \cf0 Using in-app dunning messages to catch active users\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 If someone\'92s using your product, they\'92re already engaged\'97so why not remind them right there? In-app dunning messages are a great way to reach customers with overdue payments 
\f1\i while
\f0\i0  they\'92re interacting with your platform.\
It reduces friction: they can review billing information or update a payment method in just a click or two. These messages can be personalized to include the customer\'92s payment details, upcoming due dates, or even a friendly final notice.\
Since users can\'92t unsubscribe from in-app prompts, they\'92re perfect for high-visibility payment reminders without interrupting the customer experience.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs28 \cf0 SMS and push notifications: quick nudges for overdue payments\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 SMS and push notifications are great for short, timely reminders\'97especially when a due date is looming or a payment fails. These channels are perfect for encouraging prompt attention to a billing issue, particularly when email hasn\'92t worked. You might send a push after a second failed attempt or an SMS as a last-chance final notice.\
Keep the message concise, link directly to the payment page, and avoid sounding too aggressive. These nudges can dramatically reduce non payment and service interruption\'97especially when combined with more detailed emails or in-app dunning messages.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs36 \cf0 Building trust into your dunning management process\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 Trust plays a huge role in whether or not a customer follows through on a payment. If your dunning emails feel shady, cold, or confusing, people might hesitate\'97especially with billing information involved.\
That\'92s why I always focus on transparency: clearly stating the issue, showing the amount due, and linking directly to a secure payment page. I also recommend keeping the tone supportive and adding contact info in case someone needs help.\
Small things like these build confidence and reinforce that you're not just chasing money\'97you\'92re working to keep the customer relationship intact.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs36 \cf0 The role of your customer service team\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 Even with the best automated dunning emails, there are times when real human support makes all the difference.\
Your customer service team is your safety net for edge cases: confused customers, billing errors, or tricky payment failures. I\'92ve seen firsthand how a fast, friendly reply can rescue an {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.digistorms.com/blog/customer-churn-prediction"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 \ul \ulc3 \strokec3 account that might have churned}}. It\'92s important to make it easy for people to reach out\'97whether that\'92s through chat, email, or a clear \'93Need help?\'94 link in your emails.\
Dunning is part of customer communication, and support plays a key role in closing the loop.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs36 \cf0 Dunning doesn\'92t have to be awkward \'97 just human\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 I get it\'97asking someone for money is uncomfortable. But dunning emails don\'92t need to feel like collections notices from the 1800s.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li800\fi-800\ri800\sa240\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \strokec2 \uc0\u55357 \u56481  When done right, they\'92re just helpful reminders that say, \'93Hey, something went wrong\'97here\'92s how to fix it.\'94 That\'92s why I focus on making mine sound like me: human, warm, and respectful. Add a little empathy, avoid the guilt-trip language, and always explain what\'92s at stake (like losing access or interrupting service).\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0
